Agent EVAL Report
================

Date: 2026-06-10
Branch: research/embedding-branch vs main (baseline)
Seed vault: vidbrain_vault (713 notes)
Test videos: 8 (all technical: 极海Channel + 课代表立正)
Valid pairs: 8 (0 skipped)

Results:
  dim A (terminology):  -0.62  (main wins)
  dim B (wikilinks):    -0.62  (main wins, improved from -0.94 after wikilink format fix)
  dim C (suggestions):  +0.00  (tie)
  dim D (overall):      emb 0% win rate

Self-doubt: dim B flagged in 62% of reviews, dim A flagged in 38%

Conclusion: INSUFFICIENT_DATA (8 pairs, all emb losses)

Root cause:
  RAG retrieval injects vault content into Agent prompts, but the injected
  context does not translate into measurable quality improvement. After
  fixing the [[wikilink]] format pollution bug, dim B improved from -0.94
  to -0.62 but remained negative. dim A worsened. At no point in two
  independent eval runs (36 pairs + 8 pairs) did embedding-branch win
  a single dimension D comparison.

  The hypothesis that "RAG-augmented prompts produce better Agent output"
  is falsified for this product context (Chinese tech talk ASR → structured
  Obsidian notes). The embedding infrastructure (chunk store, similarity
  search) works correctly, but the prompt engineering surface does not
  benefit from the additional context.

Decision: DO NOT MERGE research/embedding-branch.
